    Chlorthalidone vs. Hydrochlorothiazide for Hypertension-Cardiovascular Events.
In this large pragmatic trial of thiazide diuretics at doses commonly used in clinical practice, patients who received chlorthalidone did not have a lower occurrence of major cardiovascular outcome events or non-cancer-related deaths than patients who received hydrochlorothiazide. (Funded by the Veterans Affairs Cooperative Studies Program;  ClinicalTrials.gov number, NCT02185417.).
